    "created_at": "2025-05-06T23:39:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-06T23:39:19Z",
    "body": "I have a custom command version for macOS, as a placeholder for anyone that stumbles upon this thread:\n\n`[custom.angular]`\n`description = 'angular version support'`\n`require_repo = true`\n`when = \"\"\"\ngrep -q '\"@angular/core\"' package.json && exit 0 || exit 1\n\"\"\"`\n`shell = [\"bash\", \"--noprofile\", \"--norc\"]`\n`command = \"\"\"\ncat package.json | grep '\"@angular/core\"' | awk -F: '{ gsub(/[^0-9.]/, \"\", $2); print $2 }'\n\"\"\"`\n`format = \"( v$output)\"`\n\nTweakable enough, I believe. Hopefully it gets implemented out of the box. 👍 ",
